Detect bid invitations and auto-block calendar at the bid deadline

Adds first-class handling of construction-style bid requests (RFP/RFQ/ITB,
"please submit a bid", "plans attached for bid", etc.) alongside the
existing meeting-request detection.

Analyzer (analyzer.py)
- Analysis schema gains: is_bid_request, bid_confidence, bid_project_name,
  bid_project_location, bid_due_date_iso, bid_scope_summary, bid_contact.
- Renamed `confidence` -> `meeting_confidence`; backward-compat .confidence
  property aliases meeting_confidence so any external readers keep working.
- New _SYSTEM_PROMPT_TEMPLATE teaches the LLM to classify on TWO independent
  axes (meeting + bid). It is parameterized with the user's company name
  and aliases so "BPC, please bid this" gets recognized as targeted, not
  generic mass invitation.
- _company_context() helper formats the prompt section.
- New derive_bid_reminder_window() returns a (start, end) at the bid due
  time, returning None when the deadline is already past.

Agent loop (main.py)
- Passes company_name + company_aliases to EmailAnalyzer.
- _process_one() now runs two independent calendar actions:
    * meeting block (existing): at proposed meeting time.
    * bid reminder (new):       30-min event titled "BID DUE: <project>"
                                placed AT the bid deadline.
  Both are gated by AUTO_BLOCK_CONFIDENCE; bid reminder additionally gated
  by AUTO_BLOCK_BID_REMINDER (default on).
- Notification body now reflects whichever action(s) fired.
- State store records max(meeting_confidence, bid_confidence) for dedup.

Config + .env.example
- New: COMPANY_NAME, COMPANY_ALIASES, AUTO_BLOCK_BID_REMINDER.
- Settings.email_provider given default "outlook" so dataclass field
  ordering stays valid as new defaulted fields land.

Wizard (setup_wizard.py)
- Section 1 now also asks for company name + comma-separated aliases.

Tests (tests/test_analyzer.py)
- All existing meeting tests updated to use meeting_confidence.
- New tests cover: bid window in future, bid in past, no due date,
  ISO normalization, confidence range validation, company-context helper.
- 9 new tests, total 16/16 pass.

README
- Top-of-doc summary updated to mention bid handling.
- New "Bid request handling" section explains signals, calendar action,
  and tunable env vars.
- Config reference updated.
